page.title: 05MammalsFishReptiles;Murlough
page.content: Apart from the rabbits, the mammal population includes Foxes and Stoats, Badgers, Field Mice and Pygmy Shrews. Hedgehogs, Otters and Hares are rare visitors. This year Otters were sighted at 402355 on three occasions. The Common Seal is the typical seal of the area, 100 or so breeding just outside the block to the East but using the relatively undisturbed beach at 420350 to bask. A few Grey seals are also often seen but they do not breed locally. Salmon and trout are caught in the Dundrum Bay, Mullet are common in the shallower waters of the Inner Bay and Sand Eels spawn in large numbers along the sides of the channel and Millet and Eels are also caught. The Common Lizard has been seen occasionally in the dunes as has the Cmmon Newt.Common Frogs breed in pond.
